  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6553.98 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma concentration (6530-6550 strikes all showing -9B to -21B), dealers are being forced to buy this rally aggressively as their short gamma positions move against them. The breakout regime with -99.7B total GEX means dealers will continue amplifying moves—they're buying strength here and will sell any dips hard, creating explosive two-way volatility. Key inflection at 6580 where positive gamma kicks in and dealer behavior flips to selling rallies, while 6550 remains the critical amplification zone with -21.2B in negative gamma.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent moves in both directions with dealers forced to chase price action.",
